 According to information from a trusted source, five members of a Special Task Force were operational in the reserve on Saturday. The operation was planned after information from Crime Intelligence that poachers planned to target rhinos in the reserve. Around 21:00, poachers and task force members were involved in a confrontation. The poachers opened fire and police retaliated. In the process two men were shot and killed and a member of the task force was injured.
He was transported to Life Midmed Hospital to be stabilized before he was moved to a hospital in Gauteng. Also read: Poachers killed in shootout with police Items, described as ‘poaching equipment’ were found on the scene, including a hunting rifle. Crime Air Network Initiative reported that ammunition as well as night vision optical equipment were also confiscated. Ammunition, along with other poaching equipment was confiscated. Capt. Khanyisile Zwane, Middelburg police spokesperson, confirmed that two inquest dockets and one of attempted murder are currently being investigated by the Middelburg Police.  Abandoned baby found alive, rushed to hospital Hijackers at large in Middelburg Suid-Afrikaanse spiesgooi kampioen dalk vir muti vermoor Kaptyn Booyse die kroek  • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za